computeX

public void computeX(TimelineRenderingContext context)
Description copied from interface: EventHorizontalLocator
Computes the list of events and their horizontal (X axis) position that fit in the current visible "frame": TimelineRenderingContext.getViewStartX() to TimelineRenderingContext.getViewEndX().

The contract of this method guarantees TimelineRenderingContext.setFirtEventIndex(int) , TimelineRenderingContext.setLastEventIndex(int) , and TimelineRenderingContext.setEventsX(org.codeandmagic.util.FakeArrayFloat) will be called during the execution of this function.

Specified by:
computeX in interface EventHorizontalLocator
